                <p><bibl><ptr target="#pernier1931"/>, p. <citedRange>208</citedRange></bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>9.120</citedRange></bibl>; 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#robert1955"/>, p. <citedRange>28</citedRange></bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>14.890</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>020700</citedRange></bibl>.</p>        
                <p>Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#cdl2020"/>, p.<citedRange>245-248</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#rosamilia2023"/>, pp. <citedRange>83-85</citedRange></bibl>.</p></div>
            <div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><space quantity="10" unit="character"/> Τὰν <w lemma="ὀπά">ὀπάν</w> <space atLeast="2" unit="character"/> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>La porte <supplied reason="subaudible">a été consacrée par Untel</supplied>.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>The door <supplied reason="subaudible">was dedicated by So-and-so</supplied>.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>La porta <supplied reason="subaudible">è stata dedicata dal tale</supplied>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p>الباب (يفهم ضمنياً أنه: أهدي من قبل فلان وفلان).</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>About <foreign xml:lang="grc">ὀπά</foreign> see <bibl><ptr target="#robert1955"/></bibl> and especially at Cyrene <bibl><ptr target="#rosamilia2023"/></bibl>.</p>
                <p>We have here the word and its support restituted in its original function: the architrave of the door leading from the pronaos to the cella of the 2nd-phase Artemision.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
